com.clxcommunications.xms.api

Class MtBatchSmsResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.clxcommunications.xms.api.MtBatchSmsResult
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MtBatchBinarySmsResult, MtBatchTextSmsResult

    public abstract class MtBatchSmsResult
extends Object
    Base class for batch description classes. This contains the fields common for both textual and binary batches.

      • asTextBatch

        public final MtBatchTextSmsResult asTextBatch()
        Casts and returns this batch as a text batch. Note, if this object is not actually a text batch then this will throw a ClassCastException.

        Use of this method should typically be preceded by a call to isTextBatch(). For example 

         if (batch.isTextBatch()) {
     String body = batch.asTextBatch().body();
 }
        Returns:
        this object cast to a text batch
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - if this is not actually a text batch

      • asBinaryBatch

        public final MtBatchBinarySmsResult asBinaryBatch()
        Casts and returns this batch as a binary batch. Note, if this object is not actually a binary batch then this will throw a ClassCastException.

        Use of this method should typically be preceded by a call to isBinaryBatch(). For example 

         if (batch.isBinaryBatch()) {
     byte[] body = batch.asBinaryBatch().body();
 }
        Returns:
        this object cast to a binary batch
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - if this is not actually a binary batch
